The murder of six-year-old Stacey Adams has sent shockwaves through the community of Mitchells Plain‚ Cape Town‚ and across the country. The girl - described as a bubbly child who loved dancing - went missing from her home on Saturday. Her body was found on Sunday‚ buried in a hastily dug shallow grave. A neighbour is a suspect in her murder. On Tuesday‚ Stacey was mourned at her funeral. Grief‚ sorrow and sadness overflowed. TimesLIVE photographer Esa Alexander captured the emotions.